      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesized hemolysis model credibility from prior pump CFD studies",
      "description": "This validation result consolidates findings from multiple prior independent CFD hemolysis studies on rotary blood pumps, including published benchmark comparisons, inter-laboratory reproducibility assessments, and turbulence model sensitivity analyses. The synthesis spans over 15 peer-reviewed publications from 2010–2023 and represents a broad evidentiary base supporting the power-law hemolysis damage model used in the present COU. The aggregated evidence strongly corroborates the model's predictive fidelity across a range of pump geometries and operating regimes consistent with CPB conditions.",
